bib_record.title: Survey of 600 MeV proton cross-sections for spallogenic radionuclides in quartz-,Fe-,Co- and Ni-targets.

free_txt: .The resulting cross sections are compared with
literature values.
100 cc Ge(Li) detector (resolution 2.2 keV at
1332 keV). The detector efficiency was determined with
calibrated gamma-sources including 22Na, 54Mn, 57Co,
133Ba, 137Cs, 266Ra, and 241Am.
The errors include:
* uncertainty of counting statistics,
* uncertainty of peak area
* uncertainty of efficiency determination
* uncertainty of gamma-branching ratios
* uncertainty of half-lives
* uncertainty of monitor reaction except Co target.
Flux was 3.76 x 10**11 p/sec. The irradiation period
was 15.05 h.
The targets were fixed in form of a
sandwich in the beam center in front of a "thick
target" of quasi-lunar composition of the dimensions
30 x 30 x 180 cm for checking possible influence of
backscattered secondary nucleons
- A possible influence
of backscattered secondary nucleons was checked by
means of a model calculation for target assembly
Tbl.1 from RRL,21,293,1975

4.4+-1.1 mb is very good agreement with data of
